      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, setting up an escrow account is like preparing a treasure chest for your new home, ensuring that all the gold coins (or in this case, money) are safely stored until the grand day of closing. In the world of real estate, an escrow account is a secure holding place for your funds, managed by a neutral third party, often a title company or an escrow agent. This way, neither the buyer nor the seller can claim the treasure until all the conditions of the deal are met, like a magical pact between goblins and humans. It's a safeguard to ensure that both parties fulfill their promises, like making sure the goblin king gets his share of the gold before the humans can take their cut. So, in essence, it's a way to keep the peace and ensure that everyone gets what they're due, without any goblin shenanigans.",
